Class BatfishException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • org.batfish.common.BatfishException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BdpOscillationException, BestPathSelectionException, CircularReferenceException, CleanBatfishException, DebugBatfishException, ParserBatfishException, PedanticBatfishException, QuestionException, RedFlagBatfishException, UndefinedGroupBatfishException, UndefinedReferenceException, UnimplementedBatfishException, VendorConversionException

    public class BatfishException
extends RuntimeException
    Thrown as a fatal exception. When caught, Batfish should perform any necessary cleanup and terminate gracefully with a non-zero exit status. A BatfishException should always contain a detail message.
